00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.680
In today's Q3 planning meeting, the team discussed improving both technical reliability

00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:10.800
and user experience for our mobile payment solution. Engineering proposed migrating parts

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:15.680
of the back-end to microservices to boost scalability and adding real-time fraud detection

00:00:15.680 --> 00:00:21.520
using machine learning. The design team emphasized faster checkout flows and suggested reducing

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:27.520
confirmation steps. They also recommended adding biometric authentication options like face ID

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:32.480
and fingerprint login. Marketing highlighted that smoother payments drive retention and

00:00:32.480 --> 00:00:37.439
customer satisfaction. The group agreed that technical upgrades and UX enhancements should

00:00:37.439 --> 00:00:42.959
move forward in parallel with coordination across engineering, design, and marketing.


